title: Hi Kate! Sleep ‚Äúregression‚Äù can
post_data: Hi Kate! Sleep ‚Äúregression‚Äù can really happen at any age, but toddlers are pretty notorious for developing staging sleep rebellions (and rebellions..or dramas...in general). Part of the reason is because they are, as creatures of habit, super sensitive to even the slightest change. Which makes me... Is there such a thing as a 2 year old sleep regression?? We are 2 weeks away from 2nd birthday and he absolutely will not go to bed suddenly with out all night long drama. When he finally falls asleep he wakes up in 2-3 hrs for another repeat. He nods his head when asked if scared but i have no idea what scares him. We still use the same night light and sound machine and there are no new changes to his room. Only new thing is my husband had been gone frequently on short deployments these past 5...

title: Hi! If baby seems fine
post_data: Hi! If baby seems fine and is acting normally then sounds like he was just startled. title: Hi Brianna! Definitely bassinet to
post_data: Hi Brianna! Definitely bassinet to crib is a big transition...from the cozy and snug to the wide open spaces! She is also most likely used to be close to you. It‚Äôs actually recommended for babies to sleep in the same room as parents for the first 6 months at least, just since it‚Äôs considered safer.... Need some advice. Our 3 month old is on day two of being in her room in the crib at night. So far she moves all night, she did not do that in our room. She is also waking up now 2 times instead of the usually 1 time. She is still being swaddled and she is trying to bust out. But during the day, she doesn‚Äôt even move. Is it the change? Should we give it a week. Is the bassinet just more snug and she is having a hard time with the change?
